y states that the purchase price per share for employee and shareholder repurchases is always equal to the **then-current fair market value** at the time of the transaction. \n*   **Preferred Stock Pricing:** The unrelated 2024 repurchases of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock from existing shareholders were similarly executed at their **then-current fair market value**.\n*   **Deemed Dividend (EPS Impact):** For the purposes of calculating Earnings Per Share (EPS), the excess of the fair market value over the consideration transferred for the repurchase of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was treated as a **deemed dividend**. This accounting treatment resulted in an adjustment (an increase to net loss or decrease to net income) attributable to common shareholders.\n\n*(Note: While the filing does not publish a standalone table of the exact "fair market value per share" on specific dates, the strict policy dictates that the repurchase price equals the FMV. Based on the disclosed totals, the implied average FMV per share was approximately **$23.77** for SpaceX Common Stock in 2024, **$37.29** for SpaceX Common Stock in 2025, and **$50.85** for xAI Common Stock in 2025).*',
